<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Buffer Overflow on The Mess Of Nebula</title><link>http://evalevanto.github.io/tags/buffer-overflow/</link><description>Recent content in Buffer Overflow on The Mess Of Nebula</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>© 2026 Eva Levanto</copyright><lastBuildDate>Wed, 04 Nov 2020 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="http://evalevanto.github.io/tags/buffer-overflow/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>MicroCorruption: Santa Cruz</title><link>http://evalevanto.github.io/posts/microcorruption-cruz/</link><pubDate>Wed, 04 Nov 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://evalevanto.github.io/posts/microcorruption-cruz/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cruz/cruz.jpg"&gt;&lt;img class="img" src="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cruz/cruz.jpg"
 alt/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nice! Here is a lock. This is the manual:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cruz/santa-details.png"&gt;&lt;img class="img" src="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cruz/santa-details.png"
 alt/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passwords that are &lt;strong&gt;too long are rejected&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is not much clues from the manual.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;main&lt;/code&gt; function just calls the &lt;code&gt;login&lt;/code&gt; function:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cruz/santa-login.png"&gt;&lt;img class="img" src="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cruz/santa-login.png"
 alt/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Authentication requires a username and password input. The prompt states that these inputs should be between 8 and 16 chars. :D&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bytes &lt;code&gt;0x0, 0x8 and 0x10&lt;/code&gt; are set into the addresses at &lt;code&gt;r4 - (0x6, 0x19,0x18)&lt;/code&gt; respectively. This will probably make sense soon.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>MicroCorruption: Cusco</title><link>http://evalevanto.github.io/posts/microcorruption-cusco/</link><pubDate>Wed, 26 Aug 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://evalevanto.github.io/posts/microcorruption-cusco/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cusco/cusco.jpg"&gt;&lt;img class="img" src="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cusco/cusco.jpg"
 alt/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cusco/cusco-details.png"&gt;&lt;img class="img" src="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cusco/cusco-details.png"
 alt/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this manual, you notice that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This lock is attached to &lt;strong&gt;HSM-1&lt;/strong&gt; module.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;conditional flag&lt;/strong&gt; that accidentally gets set when very long passwords are put in, has been &lt;strong&gt;removed&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cusco/cusco-test-inpput.png"&gt;&lt;img class="img" src="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cusco/cusco-test-inpput.png"
 alt/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After a &lt;em&gt;fast fail&lt;/em&gt; using a test input: &lt;code&gt;aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa&lt;/code&gt;, turns out the program does not exit. It instead, loops back to the start of the program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cusco/cusco-loop-second-login.png"&gt;&lt;img class="img" src="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/cusco/cusco-loop-second-login.png"
 alt/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is interesting. Why? Because it is a &lt;strong&gt;clue&lt;/strong&gt; that at some point at the end of a failed password verification; instead of a program exit, the return address points to the beginning instruction to jump to. This shall become clear soon.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>MicroCorruption: Hanoi</title><link>http://evalevanto.github.io/posts/microcorruption-hanoi/</link><pubDate>Wed, 26 Aug 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://evalevanto.github.io/posts/microcorruption-hanoi/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/hanoi/hanoi.png"&gt;&lt;img class="img" src="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/hanoi/hanoi.png"
 alt/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You get to Hanoi, you find a manual.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/hanoi/hanoi-details.png"&gt;&lt;img class="img" src="http://evalevanto.github.io/images/microcorruption/hanoi/hanoi-details.png"
 alt/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Things are a bit different this time:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This Lock is attached to LockIT Pro &lt;strong&gt;HSM-1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Password &lt;strong&gt;stored in the HSM&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Password set by connecting to app through the HSM and restarting the Lock.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A flag is set&lt;/strong&gt; by the HSM after validating a correct password input.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;main&lt;/code&gt; function just calls the &lt;code&gt;login&lt;/code&gt; function. The prompt for writing your test input gives an interesting clue: the password range.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>